<p>From SSIS data tools we have a connection to mysql database with ADO.NET source component, with the following connection sting: server=123.123.123.123;user id=username;database=databasename;connectiontimeout=9000;</p>  <p>RetainSameConnection:False SupportsDTCTransations: True</p>  <p>The problem is that the schedules jobs and the manual executed jobs are failing randomly (50%-50% ) with the following message Error: ADO NET Source has failed to acquire the connection  with the following error message: "Unable to connect to any of the specified MySQL hosts.".</p>